Question 07
  1.Find b such that E[X] = c
    Given:  
    a = 5, c = 11, E[X] = c = 11  
    PERT mean formula:  
    E[X] = (a + 4c + b)/6 = 11  

    Substitute:  
    (5 + 44 + b)/6 = 11  
    (49 + b)/6 = 11  
    49 + b = 66  
    b = 17

  2.Variance approximation:Var(X) ≈ (E[X] − a)(b − E[X]) / 7  
    = (11 − 5)(17 − 11) / 7  
    = (6 × 6) / 7 = 36/7 ≈ 5.14 days²

    Variance is relatively large because the distribution is forced to have mean = mode with a wide range (5 to 17).  
    Intuition: If the most likely time equals the average, the distribution is roughly symmetric but still spread out.
